    "markdown": "---\nformat:\n  html:\n    css: styles.css\n    embed-resources: TRUE\n    code-fold: true\n    page-layout: full\n    fig_caption: yes\n---\n\n\n\n\n<br>\n<div id=\"state-body-section\">\n\n::: {.panel-tabset .nav-pills}\n\n# Parole Eligibility\n\n## How Parole Eligibility is Determined\n\nIn general, parole eligibility occurs after serving 1/3 of the total sentence, and after a minimum of  9 months. Inmates serving 21 years or more, but not a life sentence, become eligible after serving a 7 year term. In addition, inmates convicted of certain serious crimes (e.g. aggravated assault, incest, drug trafficking) are not eligible for parole until they have served 7 years or 1/3 of the prison term, whichever comes first.\n<div class=\"divider\"></div>\n\n## In Prison Past Their Parole Eligibility Date\n\nIn 2020, there were 11,827 people were in prison past their parole eligibility date. This group made up 46% of people in prison for new crimes and with sentence lengths between 1 to 25 years.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"grid-container\" style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); grid-gap: 20px;\">\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">46%</div>\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">11,827</div>\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">5</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Pct. of People in Prison<br>Past Their Parole Eligibility Date</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\" style=\"text-align: left;\">In Prison Past Their<br>Parole Eligibility Date</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Parole Board Members</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<br/>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"visualization\">\n<div id=\"htmlwidget-2556f455294d1cd2b749\" style=\"width:100%;height:175px;\" class=\"highchart html-widget \"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-2556f455294d1cd2b749\">{\"x\":{\"hc_opts\":{\"chart\"